                    '4' => 'Thorough clearance analysis: performs a detailed calculation — at 740 cm gauge reading the clearance is 1.2m, with the water rising at approximately 6.7 cm/hour (80 cm over 12 hours), in the 3 hours to reach the bridge the water will have risen approximately 20 cm, reducing clearance to approximately 1.0m, but this assumes a linear rise rate which may not hold, applies a safety margin for vessel motion (sinkage due to speed, wave wash, measurement uncertainty), determines that the effective safe clearance after margins is approximately 0.6-0.8m, which the projected 1.0m barely satisfies, monitors the gauge trend continuously and recalculates at regular intervals, has a plan for what to do if the clearance becomes unsafe before reaching the bridge (turn around at a specific point where there is room to manoeuvre the 135m convoy).',
